GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 530
Short Title: Funds/Halifax, Northampton, Warren Counties. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative R. Pierce.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Appropriations, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
March 27, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO APPROPRIATE FUNDS FOR VARIOUS PUBLIC PURPOSES IN HALIFAX,
3 NORTHAMPTON, AND WARREN COUNTIES.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5
6 PART I. HALIFAX COUNTY PUBLIC PROJECTS
7 SECTION 1.(a) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
8 Budget and Management the sum of one hundred fifteen million two hundred eleven thousand
9 seven hundred sixty-three dollars ($115,211,763) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal
10 year to provide the following directed grants to the following entities:
11 (1) Six hundred ten thousand nine hundred forty-four dollars ($610,944) to the
12 City of Roanoke Rapids for Chaloner Bridge replacement and drainage
13 improvements.
14 (2) Forty-five million two hundred eighty thousand eight hundred nineteen
15 dollars ($45,280,819) to the Roanoke Rapids Sanitary District to be allocated
16 as follows:
17 a. Four million eight hundred forty-seven thousand eight hundred
18 nineteen dollars ($4,847,819) for the Belmont Pump Station.
19 b. Six million two hundred eighteen thousand dollars ($6,218,000) for
20 the Premier Boulevard water/sewer extension.
21 c. Thirty-one million one hundred fifteen thousand dollars ($31,115,000)
22 for a drinking water emerging construction project.
23 d. Three million one hundred thousand dollars ($3,100,000) for an
24 activated sludge blower system.
25 (3) Eight million dollars ($8,000,000) to the Town of Enfield for its electric grid
26 replacement.
27 (4) Sixty-one million three hundred twenty thousand dollars ($61,320,000) to
28 Halifax County to be allocated as follows:
29 a. Five million dollars ($5,000,000) for sewer line extension to Exit 154
30 on I-95.
31 b. Three hundred twenty thousand dollars ($320,000) for Airboss access
32 road.
33 c. Five million dollars ($5,000,000) for court services building
34 renovation.
35 d. Fifty million dollars ($50,000,000) for a new county detention center.
