1 e. One million dollars ($1,000,000) for broadband service expansion.
2 SECTION 1.(b) There is appropriated to the Office of State Budget and
3 Management the sum of four million six hundred fifty thousand one hundred seventy-six dollars
4 ($4,650,176) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide the following
5 directed grants:
6 (1) Five hundred fifty thousand dollars ($550,000) to Halifax County to be
7 allocated as follows:
8 a. Three hundred fifty thousand dollars ($350,000) for a new ambulance.
9 b. Two hundred thousand dollars ($200,000) for 18 self-contained
10 breathing apparatus for the Darlington Volunteer Fire Department.
11 (2) Seven hundred thousand dollars ($700,000) to Halifax Fire and Rescue, Inc.,
12 to purchase a fire truck.
13 (3) One hundred fifty thousand dollars ($150,000) to the Town of Enfield to upfit
14 fitness building and purchase apparatus for the Fire Department.
15 (4) Fifteen thousand one hundred seventy-six dollars ($15,176) to the Town of
16 Scotland Neck to purchase body cameras and other needed equipment for the
17 Police Department.
18 (5) Two million two hundred ten thousand dollars ($2,210,000) to the Town of
19 Roanoke Rapids for needs of its fire department, including a new ladder truck,
20 generator, and air packs.
21 (6) One million twenty-five thousand dollars ($1,025,000) to the Town of Weldon
22 to be allocated as follows:
23 a. Eight hundred fifty thousand dollars ($850,000) for a new fire engine.
24 b. One hundred seventy-five thousand dollars ($175,000) for building
25 renovation and site preparation and a viper radio system purchase.
26
27 PART II. NORTHAMPTON COUNTY PUBLIC PROJECTS
28 SECTION 2.(a) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
29 Budget and Management the sum of thirteen million fifty thousand dollars ($13,050,000) in
30 nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide directed grants to the following
31 entities:
32 (1) Four hundred thousand dollars ($400,000) to the Town of Rich Square for
33 wastewater treatment improvements.
34 (2) Seven million dollars ($7,000,000) to the Town of Garysburg for water system
35 improvements.
36 (3) Two million one hundred fifty thousand dollars ($2,150,000) to the Town of
37 Seaboard to be allocated as follows:
38 a. Five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000) for Community Center
39 renovation.
40 b. One million two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($1,250,000) for street
41 replacement and repairs.
42 c. Four hundred thousand dollars ($400,000) for renovation of the Old
43 Seaboard Bank.
44 (4) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) to the Town of Woodland for the
45 construction of a new town hall.
46 (5) One million five hundred thousand dollars ($1,500,000) to Northampton
47 County for wastewater treatment expansion.
48 SECTION 2.(b) There is appropriated to the Office of State Budget and
49 Management the sum of four million seven hundred fifty-six thousand dollars ($4,756,000) in
50 nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide the following directed grants:
