29 PART IV. LAKE GASTON
30 SECTION 4. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
31 Budget and Management the sum of three hundred thousand dollars ($300,000) in recurring
32 funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to be used for a multiyear project to treat
33 lyngbya spp., a cyanobacteria, in Lake Gaston.
34
35 PART V. EFFECTIVE DATE
36 SECTION 5. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
